1
00:00:03,203 --> 00:00:18,203
Open "initial_position" project file (.NTW), this will open all the bones in their original orientation and position in space

2
00:00:24,969 --> 00:00:26,969
All 3D surfaces are now opened

3
00:00:28,022 --> 00:00:31,155
Mouse roll middle button to zoom-in or zoom-out

4
00:00:32,806 --> 00:00:34,873
You may decide to hide the grid

5
00:00:34,923 --> 00:00:36,856
Let's change lighting options

6
00:00:41,664 --> 00:00:44,664
Open the "edit first selected surface" window

7
00:00:47,897 --> 00:00:51,764
Click on the arrows to browse through all opened surfaces

8
00:00:54,518 --> 00:00:59,985
Right click + drag mouse to select manually one or several surface objects at once

9
00:01:01,235 --> 00:01:05,635
In "Move selected objects  mode", CTRL + mouse middle button drag translates the camera

10
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:11,499
Now in "Camera mode", CTRL + mouse middle button drage will translate selected objects

11
00:01:15,518 --> 00:01:19,918
Use also the yellow sliders to rotate / translate selected objects

12
00:01:26,005 --> 00:01:28,005
CTRL + middle click drag to translate the left mandible

13
00:01:28,582 --> 00:01:32,715
Yellow slider to rotate left mandible along the z viewing axis

14
00:01:33,205 --> 00:01:37,338
Yellow slider to rotate left mandible along the y viewing axis

15
00:01:41,789 --> 00:01:45,122
CTRL + middle click drag to translate the mandible

16
00:02:02,016 --> 00:02:04,116
Several vertebrae are now selected at once

17
00:02:04,188 --> 00:02:06,688
CTRL + middle click drag to translate all selected vertebrae at once

18
00:02:07,226 --> 00:02:13,426
Select the 2 remaining caudal vertebrae and translate them as well (CTRL + middle click drag)

19
00:02:26,072 --> 00:02:33,872
In "Move selected objects" mode, no need to press "CTRL", Left mouse button drag is enough to rotate selected objects

20
00:02:41,126 --> 00:02:43,593
Now let's select every objects (alternative: CTRL+A), and delete them (DEL button)

21
00:02:45,595 --> 00:02:49,128
Now open the "anatomical_position" project (NTW file)

22
00:03:05,058 --> 00:03:10,058
Now all bones are given a "biologically relevant" orientation and position.

23
00:03:14,886 --> 00:03:20,286
Let's browse through the  vertebrae

24
00:03:43,548 --> 00:03:45,681
Select the cranium and mandibles

25
00:03:45,729 --> 00:03:48,729
Translate the cranium and mandibles ("Move selected obejcts" mode, then middle click drag)

26
00:03:50,141 --> 00:03:54,274
This last action can be undone (click on undone or "CTRL + Z")

